{"data": {"repository": {"pullRequest": {"id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTAwODM4ODA3", "number": 8027, "title": "Add Support for In Text Citations", "bodyText": "Intent\nPandoc-citeproc supports citations of both note and in text style citations (as does CSL). Previously, we always used the note form like [@cite]. We now support the in-text form as well, which can be either @cite or @cite [suffix]. Users may use any of the forms and expect completions, formatting, and so on to be respected and work properly. In addition, when users are inserting citations using the insert citation dialog, they may choose to use the in-text style if they are only selecting a single citation.\nCitations are reversible by using the backspace key (e.g. if you mean to type a GitHub name or twitter handle you can just backspace to 'break' the citation.\nApproach\nWe did some plumbing to break any assumptions that citations were always enclosed by brackets. We ensured that the in-text form don't conflict with crossrefs.\nQA Notes\n\nCitation entries will now be blue in color, as links, cross refs.\nCitation entries are valid of the following types of forms:\n\n[@cite]\n[@cite; and some text @cite2]\nThis is some text @cite and some more text.\nThis is some text @cite [page 23] and more text.", "createdAt": "2020-10-09T21:58:43Z", "url": "https://github.com/rstudio/rstudio/pull/8027", "merged": true, "mergeCommit": {"oid": "592ab81871d5e5375d5711f152de189619628b88"}, "closed": true, "closedAt": "2020-10-09T22:11:02Z", "author": {"login": "dragonstyle"}, "timelineItems": {"totalCount": 16, "pageInfo": {"startCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdQjO6DgH2gAyNTAwODM4ODA3OmVmOGM4ZDFjOGY1ODkxNmM1ZTI3ZTg1N2UyZjEzNzI4NzM0NWYxZmE=", "endCursor": "Y3Vyc29yOnYyOpPPAAABdQ9lTvgFqTUwNjAxMTA4MA==", "hasNextPage": false, "hasPreviousPage": false}, "nodes": [{"__typename": "PullRequestCommit", "commit": {"oid": "ef8c8d1c8f58916c5e27e857e2f137287345f1fa", "author": {"user": {"login": "jjallaire", "name": "J.J. Allaire